# Notifications & operational hooks

Four ways a job talks to humans/systems.

- **Email** — start / success / failure / duration warning / backlog (job-level)
- **Webhooks / system destinations** — Slack · Teams · PagerDuty · HTTP → **paging on-call**
- **Run-as identity** — user or **service principal**; governs UC perms
- **Always-run task** — `run_if = ALL_DONE` fires on success **or** failure

## Two exam tells

- "page on-call on failure" → **webhook / system destination**, not email
- "prod job ≠ one engineer's creds" → **run as a service principal**

**Guarantee a failure alert:** job-level `on_failure`, or an `ALL_DONE` task (which can also *do work*).
